A single line function makes sense because it allows you to alter functionality later without worrying you forgot about some instance of that pattern:<p><pre><code>    def logUnexpectedError(t: Throwable) = log.error(&quot;Oops: {}&quot;, t)
</code></pre>
After I get it together and start keeping proper metrics:<p><pre><code>    def logUnexpectedError(t: Throwable) = {
      log.error(&quot;Oops: {}&quot;, t)
      statistics.errorCounterByClass(t.getClass()).inc()
    }</code></pre>
